The paper discusses the properties and location of extreme overfitting points in modern neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning applications. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, given the focus on neural networks and their training and testing accuracy, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CV and cs.AI.
